  "wikitext": "\n'''4-2-290\n\nAlternative term: Inter-site error\n\nAn error of bearing, other than source error, due to scattering or lateral deviation by irregularities in, or obstacles on, the earth's surface outside the site of the direction finder.\n\n\nNote: In ground-wave transmission such an error may be called Ground-path error or\n\nHeterogeneous ground-path error.\n\n{{IALAFooter}}\n\n{{languages|Distant site error}}\n[[Category:4.2 Radio Beacons and Direction Finding Equipment]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 1970-89 Edition]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 2023 Revision]]"
